description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to join the NHS team? Have you got an interest in science? Would you like to be paid to train?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you can answer yes to these questions then this role may be for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic individuals to train to be pharmacy technicians. You will need to be a good communicator, have good attention to detail and be able to work well within a team environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide a training role which provides on the job training and 7.5hr per week off the job training time complete your technician course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will rotate through our stores, dispensary, aseptic areas on a rotational basic across Stoke Mandeville, &amp; Wycombe Hospitals. This will give you the essential skills to complete the competencies to register as a pharmacy technician.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have robots in our stores and dispensaries &amp; are a forward thinking department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss this role further please ring Maxine Webb - Chief Technician on 01296 315283&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greg Edwards, Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : greg.edwards@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number : 07866 168267&lt;/p&gt;
